The paper deals with the construction and study of linear codes, which are primarily studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The codes also have applications in data storage systems (cs.DS) and association schemes (cs.CC), which are related to coding theory. Additionally, the paper mentions authentication codes, which are used in secure communication systems and fall under the sub-category of security and privacy (cs.SI).
